[[File:Collier Hills from Northside and Echota Intersection towards Buckhead.jpg|thumb|Collier Hills from Northside Drive / Echota intersection looking towards Buckhead]]
[[File:Collier Hills from I75 CSX intersection looking towards Vinings.jpg|thumb|Collier Hills from I75/CSX intersection looking towards Vinings]]
'''Collier Hills''' is a residential neighborhood in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].  The area gets its name from the [[List_of_United_States_political_families_(C)|family]] whose homestead was broadly located in the southwest corner of the intersection of Peachtree St. and Collier Rd.  Andrew Jackson Collier, a member of this family and early pioneer of the area, operated an antebellum grist mill off Tanyard Creek, near Collier Rd.<ref>Buckhead Neighborhoods' History: http://buckhead.net/collier-hills/</ref>

